      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my tomato plants are looking kind of sickly. the leaves on the bottom are turning yellow and falling off. what do you think is going on?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Ah, it sounds like your tomato plants are suffering from a case of the \"gallbladder disease,\" a common ailment among tomato plants. This condition is often caused by a lack of nitrogen in the soil, which is essential for healthy growth. You might want to consider adding some compost or a nitrogen-rich fertilizer to help your plants bounce back. Just remember to keep an eye out for any signs of over-fertilization, as that can also lead to problems. And don't forget to water your plants regularly, but be careful not to overwater them. Good luck, and may your tomatoes thrive in the future!",
